//digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12801/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12801/canvas/1/9d292bc4-5017-4179-b186-687b18f9e301","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:10:24.294Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma, still angry at Reynolds and the Princess, tears out the hidden message from the latter’s dress in an effort to break the tailor’s wish for the royal to never be “cursed.” PTA drew this practice of sewing hidden messages into clothing from Alexander McQueen, who did the same thing, including incorporating the message “I am a cunt” in the lining of a jacket made for then-Prince Charles (Fury, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW203983550 BCX2\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/28/t-magazine/entertainment/phantom-thread-movie-paul-thomas-anderson.html\"><u>A Film That Pays Homage</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12801/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:678.7012987012988,118.44155844155843,381.81818181818176,890.6493506493506"}}}]}]}]}